## Output Requirements

1. Follow all company rules strictly
2. At the end of your work, report results in this JSON format:
```json
{
  "status": "completed|blocked|needs_review",
  "summary": "Brief description of what was done",
  "output_files": ["list of modified/created files"],
  "next_suggestion": "Suggested next step (optional)"
}
```
3. If blocked, explain why and who can help

## IM Communication Rules

**You MUST communicate with team members via the IM system.** No other channels allowed.

### Send Messages

```bash
# Text message
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/messages/channels/<channelId> \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"senderId":"<your-employee-id>","content":"message","type":"text"}'

# Task update
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/messages/channels/<channelId> \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"senderId":"<your-employee-id>","content":"task xxx completed","type":"task_update"}'

# Code review
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/messages/channels/<channelId> \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"senderId":"<your-employee-id>","content":"review feedback...","type":"code_review"}'

# Approval request
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/messages/channels/<channelId> \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"senderId":"<your-employee-id>","content":"please approve xxx","type":"approval_request"}'
```

### Read Messages

```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/api/messages/channels/<channelId>?limit=50
```

### Rules

- All task assignments, progress reports, and discussions must happen in the project channel
- Use `task_update` type for status changes
- Use `code_review` type for code reviews
- Use `approval_request` type when approval is needed
- Report blockers in the channel and tag the responsible person
